# Project Configuration

This file defines the Jira projects, statuses, and template references used across all skills and orchestrators. Update this file when your project context changes.

---

## Jira Projects

Projects that this BA Operating System manages:

| Project Key | Name / Description |
|-------------|-------------------|
| MYPROJECT   | Replace with your project name |

---

## Refinement Assessment Statuses

When running `/assess-refinement`, the system fetches all issues from these statuses:

| Status             | Purpose                                      |
|--------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Ready for Review   | Replace with your pre-refinement status      |
| In Refinement      | Replace with your refinement status          |

---

## Issue Template References

Templates are fetched fresh from Jira every time an issue is crafted or assessed. These define the required structure for each issue type.

| Issue Type | Jira Key      | When to fetch                              |
|------------|---------------|-------------------------------------------|
| Story      | MYPROJECT-100 | When working on a user-facing need         |
| Task       | MYPROJECT-101 | When working on technical/operational work |
| Bug        | MYPROJECT-102 | When working on broken/incorrect behaviour |

---

## Quality Reference

| Resource                    | Location         | When to fetch                                    |
|-----------------------------|------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Quality Management Playbook | Confluence page ID: 0000000000 | When classifying bugs or assessing bug severity |
